    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dun</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo, Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received November 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 181.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your instruction of the 22d ultimo relative to the two
                            Japanese boys under arrest at Shanghai charged as spies.</p>
                <pb facs="0426" n="376" xml:id="pg_376"/>
                <p>In connection with the last paragraph of your instruction, in which you
                            inform me that the Chinese minister at Washington “agreed that the two
                            alleged Japanese spies should not be tried until Colonel Denby returned
                            to China,” I regret to say that the young men in question were executed
                            at Nankin on the 8th instant, before the colonel had reached
                            Shanghai.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin Dun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
